People in Dallas County will soon be required to wear face coverings when they work or shop at essential businesses and use public transit.
New Dallas County casesMeanwhile, Dallas County on Thursday reported seven new COVID-19 deaths — its second-highest daily toll — to bring the county’s total to 50.
So far, 2,066 Dallas County residents have tested positive.
Denton CountyA Flower Mound man in his 60s was the 15th Denton County resident to die of COVID-19, county health officials said Thursday.
Thirty-three county residents have tested positive for the virus, with 22 of them living in the Forney/Mesquite area.